<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-10T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-10T14:00:00-05:00" n="347" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2680</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-10T21:00:00+02:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1916, 9 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 11, 2 p.
                                    m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3873. Presented note in your 2983<note n="1" xml:id="d347fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_263">p.
                                    263</ref>.</note> to <persName corresp="#p_JGEGV1">Von
                                    Jagow</persName>, 1 [o’clock] to-day. Had a general talk with
                                him but learned nothing particular. From general information think
                                Germany will not answer this note. <persName corresp="#p_JGEGV1">Von
                                    Jagow</persName> said German note had not made any express
                                condition. It is possible <persName corresp="#p_BJHACV1">Bernstorff</persName> may be authorized to declare against
                                propaganda in America, plots, etc. Talk here of Sweden coming in. No
                                foundation apparent except that large Swedish military commission is
                                here and made much of.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>